    <item>
      <title>My Little Crony</title>
      <link>https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/post/my-little-crony/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 10 Nov 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/post/my-little-crony/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;script src=&#34;https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/rmarkdown-libs/header-attrs/header-attrs.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;link href=&#34;https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/rmarkdown-libs/anchor-sections/anchor-sections.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;
&lt;script src=&#34;https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/rmarkdown-libs/anchor-sections/anchor-sections.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;


&lt;p&gt;A visualization of the connections between &lt;strong&gt;Tory politicians&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;companies being awarded government contracts during the pandemic&lt;/strong&gt; based on a wide range of investigative reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My Little Crony has been cited in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2020-11-12/debates/D99D4A22-85F6-4297-8FF6-87EDCF67647D/BusinessOfTheHouse?highlight=little%20crony#contribution-FA294117-62BF-4B93-BDBA-86274981214D&#34;&gt;House of Commons&lt;/a&gt;, on &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bbc.co.uk/sounds/play/m000pdqs&#34;&gt;BBC Radio 4&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.globalplayer.com/catchup/lbc/uk/46vyD81/&#34;&gt;LBC&lt;/a&gt;, and covered in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://metro.co.uk/2020/11/13/my-little-crony-map-shows-deals-between-government-mps-and-tory-donors-13587900/#metro-comments-container&#34;&gt;Metro&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cityam.com/labour-calls-for-probe-into-covid-deals-between-government-and-tory-donors/&#34;&gt;City A.M.&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://bylinetimes.com/2020/11/13/what-i-learnt-about-the-great-procurement-scandal-building-my-little-crony/&#34;&gt;Byline Times&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;
&lt;iframe style=&#34;border: 0; display:block; width:100%; height:100vh; overflow:hidden;&#34; allow=&#34;fullscreen&#34; src=&#34;https://determined-panini-a6e122.netlify.app/files/crony.html&#34; title=&#34;My Little Crony&#34;&gt;
&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;guide&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Scroll&lt;/em&gt; to zoom&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Drag&lt;/em&gt; to move around&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hover&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;tap&lt;/em&gt; icons and connections for more info&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the &lt;em&gt;drop down menu&lt;/em&gt; to select highlight particular nodes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The lines represent:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: red;&#34;&gt; ― government contracts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: blue;&#34;&gt;― political donations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: grey;&#34;&gt;― other connections (e.g. family/employment)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thicker lines indicate more valuable contracts or donations.&lt;/p&gt;
